rComments: Shauna is very knowledgeable in abnormal psychology. The exams were not difficult, however, the amount of material covered was considerably more than your average course.

LOVED her. You can tell she is extremely enthusiastic about psychology. She was very clear in lectures and made sure to clarify any topic that might of been a little bit difficult.  Very approachable. She definitely knows her stuff. Although you do have to go to class to pass, the class was so interesting I didn't want to miss it.

She isn't the easiest professor, however, I guarantee that you will learn a lot if you put in the effort. She is extremely helpful during office hours. Lectures are engaging and she is super friendly! (No assigned textbook! Papers were assigned for readings but exam was mostly lecture based!!)
